Class JavaShallowParser

  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IShallowParser

    public class JavaShallowParser
extends CStyleShallowParserBase
    Shallow parser for Java.

    What this parser does and does not:

    • The parser recognizes types (classes, enums, interfaces), methods and attributes, and individual statements.
    • It recognizes the nesting of statements (e.g. in loops), but does not parse into the statements. For example, it recognizes an if-statement and provides the list of sub-statements, but does not provide direct access to the if-condition.
    • Import and package statements are parsed as meta information.
    • Annotations are recognized as meta information, but only annotations at types and methods. Annotations at parameters are not parsed, as the parser does not parse into the parameter list of methods.
    • The parser does not recognize anonymous classes. These are treated as a single long statement or attribute. Inner classes, however, are parsed correctly.
    • The parser can deal with multiple classes in a single file.
